The paper focuses on software development effort estimation using machine learning models, specifically neural network models. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper compares different neural network models, which involves optimization and tuning of hyperparameters, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks also falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with project management and decision-making, which could be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
